{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_01Qx8E5rxv9CbHzMmij47ThT","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Pipeline fixed and verified. Summary:\n\n## Root Cause\n- **Stage 3 failure**: The `spark-submit` job ran with `spark.executor.memory=256m` (268,435,456 bytes), which is **below Spark 3.5's hard minimum of 471,859,200 bytes**. Spark refused to initialize the SparkContext → `[INVALID_EXECUTOR_MEMORY]` error, manifesting as the Stage 3 OOM failure.\n- **Data skew (the underlying reason memory matters)**: From `skew_info.txt` and the diagnostic server:\n  - `total_records=100000`, `distinct_user_ids=1000`\n  - `hot_user_id=999` holds `50000` records (~50% of all data)\n  - **skew_ratio = 500x** (far exceeds the 10x threshold). The `GROUP BY user_id` aggregation in Stage 3 piles ~half the dataset onto one key, blowing the tiny 256m heap.\n\n## Fix Applied (`etl-job.yaml`)\n- Raised `spark.executor.memory` `256m → 512m` (safely above the ~450MB minimum, fits the pod limit).\n- Enabled **AQE skew handling**: `spark.sql.adaptive.enabled=true` + `spark.sql.adaptive.skewJoin.enabled=true` (directly mitigates the 500x hot-key skew).\n- Bumped the pod memory limit `1Gi → 2Gi` to give the JVM headroom.\n\nThen deleted the failed job, re-applied, and polled to completion.\n\n## Verification\n- `kubectl get job etl-job` → **STATUS: Complete (1/1)**, condition `SuccessCriteriaMet`.\n- Job logs end with the success marker: **`spark_etl_pipeline_verified`**.\n\nAll four success criteria met: OOM identified, skew diagnosed (user_id 999, 500x), fix applied (memory + AQE), and the ETL job completed successfully."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":308,"cache_creation_input_tokens":413,"cache_read_input_tokens":39169,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":413},"output_tokens":3,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"369da54a-bc42-4b12-8143-6164f5f2cdae","uuid":"721fba2a-6a4f-42cf-a194-34ac275c4f4d","request_id":"req_011CcATapCqEeEW8HJjJkp5a"}
